# Professionalization for ChambaGPT

This plan aims to take the current decentralized state to a professional level by adding industry-standard helper files, configurations, and assets management.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration and Helpers
#### [NEW] [constants.js](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Downloads/moodboard-jobs/constants.js)
Define UI strings, colors, and configuration values (like the "Oro Puro" categories) in one place to avoid magic strings in `app.js`.

#### [NEW] [utils.js](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Downloads/moodboard-jobs/utils.js)
Generic helper functions for clipboard copying, URL handling, and DOM manipulation to keep `app.js` focused on high-level logic.

### Assets and Branding
#### [NEW] [favicon.ico](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Downloads/moodboard-jobs/favicon.ico)
Add a custom skull/yellow brand icon (placeholder or generated) to make the browser tab look professional.

#### [NEW] [robots.txt](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Downloads/moodboard-jobs/robots.txt) / [sitemap.xml](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Downloads/moodboard-jobs/sitemap.xml)
Basic SEO infrastructure to make the site "indexable" by search engines.

### UI Experience
#### [MODIFY] [styles.css](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Downloads/moodboard-jobs/styles.css)
Add a "Custom Interactive Cursor" or subtle background micro-animations that respond to the mouse, giving it that "Premium" feel.

---

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Check that all scripts load without 404 errors.
- Validate that `data.js` remains compatible with the Python updater.

### Manual Verification
- Verify the new interactive effects on 1300x600 resolution.
- Ensure the SEO tags appear correctly in the head.
